          <td bgcolor="#F1F1F1" rowspan="2" valign="top" nowrap width=120> <a name="post107773"></a> 
             <font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="1"><a href="javascript:void openWhoIamWindow('/forums/whoiam.php?id=675')"><b>Barobin</b></a></font><br>
            <font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1">Journeyman<br></font><br>
            <font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1"> </font>
<br><a href="http://www.berthall.com/forums/mod/karma.php?action=points&userid=675&postid=107773" target=_blank>Karma: 16</a></td>
          <td bgcolor="#F1F1F1" width="*" valign="top"> <font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1"> 
            <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing=" 0" cellpadding=" 0">
              <tr>
                <td><img src="images/posticon.gif" border="0" alt="Old Post"> <font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1"><b></b></font></td>
                <td align="right" nowrap>&laquo; 05-04-2003 06:09 PM &raquo;</td>
              </tr>
            </table>
             </font> 
            <p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="1">To me, playing online game is to meet new interesting people.  I always thought meeting new and interesting people is what makes the initial experience of EQ so fun.  I am sure many of you went into EQ without knowing anyone close but have became friends as your jounrey thru the game.<br />
<br />
To create an Alliance/Guild/Realm before the game begin really hurt this experience.  Imagine you are a newbie, just starting a new online game.  You were trying to look for a group but you notice most of people in your lvl are from the same guild... when you sent them a tell they would not responds... heck when you are trying to kill this mob they would come and Kill Steal you.   This will wreck the newbie initial experience for the newbie.  This was very visable in DaOC and where you already have establish guilds (for ex. Afterlife) running different server and as a newbie you have no idea which server is run by who.<br />
<br />
I also understand if you have a group of people you know, you really don't have to put up with crap of ninja looter, Kill Stealer, liars etc. As well your interest on the server would be protected because your guild is the dominate... but my disagreement to the Alliance/Guild/Realm is for the newbie gamers' experience who just got enough cash to try out the many paid as you go online games.<br />
<br />
P.S. Beside how many of you really call all your guild mate friends... the guilds I was in, there are few people I haven't even talk to or interact with... just raid with... So I don't mind friends joining together in a new server but not as an alliance/guild/realm etc.</font></p>
             
            <p></p>
