            <p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="1">Group first, guild later <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt=""><br />
<br />
Case and point is my experience with Shadowbane.  I outleveled Niub in beta and did so to the point where I couldn't group with him.<br />
<br />
When the game went live, he buckled down, i took time off, and he  was way ahead of me.<br />
<br />
He had his own guild, with friends, part of an alliance.  I, at the time, was "too low" to group with them, so I made new friends and met new people, and ended finding a great gruop of people to explore and group with.<br />
<br />
Your idea has pluses and minuses - good and bad <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="">  ANd yes, it's far too early to decide, but i'm definitely for hanging out with everyone, as you'd be nuts to not play this game <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt=""></font></p>
             
